parameters.name: ANODE_USED
parameters.description: Anode used to calculate moments.  A value of 9 implies that multiple anodes were used.

parameters.name: SIGNAL_TO_NOISE
parameters.description: Signal to noise ratio threshold.  Only data values above this threshold go into the moments calculation.

parameters.name: SC_POTENTIAL
parameters.description: Spacecraft potential during the time period given

parameters.name: QUALITY_FACTOR
parameters.description: The number of standard deviations, assuming Poisson counting statistics, that the peak of the Maxwellian corresponding to the determined moments lies above the ELS one-count level.  The larger the value, the better.

parameters.name: SC_CHARGE_STATE
parameters.description: Indicates whether the data is likely to be from a region in which the spacecraft is negatively charged. 0: likely positively charged 1: likely negatively charged

parameters.name: PENETRATING_RADIATION
parameters.description: Indicates whether the data is probably from a region in which there is penetrating radiation present. 0: not likely to be present 1: likely to be present

parameters.name: DENSITY_WITHOUT_PEN_RAD
parameters.description: Density, summed over all energies, but with penetrating radiation subtracted from the data before moments calculations were made.

parameters.name: TEMPERATURE_WITHOUT_PEN_RAD
parameters.description: Temperature, summed over all energies, but with penetrating radiation subtracted from the data before moments calculations were made.

parameters.name: QUALITY_FACTOR_WITHOUT_PEN_RAD
parameters.description: The number of standard deviations, assuming Poisson counting statistics, that the peak of the Maxwellian corresponding to the determined moments lies above the ELS one-count level, but with penetrating radiation subtracted from the data before moments calculations were made.  The larger the value, the better.
